snippet.textDisplay: This season was beautiful in its own way and magically transported us to an era long lost and at the same time reflected the present amazingly. Songs like Allah hu akbar, laal meri,dam mast kalandar and maula tera noor brought us close to God. This season gave us some soulful ballads like Faasle, Muntazir,mujhse pehli si, tere naam and baanware. The essence of folk captivated us in songs like Tinak dhin, jindjaani, lathay di chadar and baaki. Ghoom tana is a story of inspiration in itself and yo soch was like a serene dream weaved with the reality of life. Katay na Katay celebrated women in the most powerful way and songs like ranjish, Ronay na diya and jaan e baharan presented heartbreak in its purest form.  Us raha par gave an important message for today's youth  - walk on your own path without fear of society. This season was an amalgamation of passion, power and purity. Although some singers like atif aslam and asim azhar were missed, this season gave us some unheard voices. Waiting an entire year is an uphill task and the true fans would relate. Till then these songs would be on repeat. And yes I am from India and I consider myself fortunate that I can relate to Pakistan 's music and understand the beautiful language.. (even if I fail to, the lyrics are there). Thank you coke studio Pakistan for keeping the rich music of the unpartitioned country alive! (qb stole the show!)

Very pleased with Ali Hamza - well done!

Tribute to Junaid was absolutely brilliant, would have been happier to see one of Junoon guys (ideally Ali Azmat) instead of Ali Zafar.

Overall Coke studio has set such a high standard that living up to it everytime is a mighty task, hence 10 was not one of the most memorable off all the seasons for me.
